title: Data Network Analysis : What to know.
description:
**About the Speaker**

Emeka is a Senior Knowledge Engineer with Cymantiks Limited, a company that makes Government, Organizations and Cities smarter using Semantic Technologies, for Data Modeling, Knowledge Representation, and Ontology Engineering, en-route to exploiting the opportunities in their data assets for Artificial Intelligence, Data Analytics to simulate human decision-making and high-level cognitive tasks that can be used to solve complex problems and achieve their desired Digital Transformation objectives.
In the last 25 years, Emeka has been at the forefront of technology and innovation in Nigeria from co-founding the earliest startup (ngex.com) to building cognitive solutions (Knowledge Graph on Disease Incidences, Legal Documents, African Films) to building Smart Agents, Software Autonomous Systems and Rules as Codes (RaC) using Semantic AI and Blockchain technology.
Emeka is able to understand and explain technologies from deep-diving under the hood to the value proposition level. He believes that Linked Data, Blockchain and AI will change and improve the way we live and work, and he is passionate about designing and building systems that will make this happen and teaching others to do this as well.
He has been listed among the top 20 most influential Technology people in Africa (2013) by South Africa IT News to name a few
He groks at the intersection of Digital Societies, Economic Development, Urbanization and Semantic AI on Twitter (@EmekaOkoye).

title: Hacknosis: Optimizing Patient Experiences
description:
# The Challenge

Gaps in healthcare still exist and the need for better solutions to bridge those gaps is critical. Today, more than half of the world‚Äôs population lives one to two hours away from a doctor. The pandemic taught us that telehealth can be a great option. It allows patients and doctors to maintain routine contact and, therefore, good health‚Äîbut only if the right tools are available. The challenge faced by health providers is how to incorporate new technologies that enable doctors and patients to have real conversations, supported by a simple experience.

### This is where you come in.

Developers are out-of-the-box thinkers, so we need your help to improve the flow of information between patients and doctors and identify ways to provide better patient support, regardless of their location.

### Tech Stack

* Teams may use any tech stack of their preference
* The tech stack should include a combination of cloud technologies, data & analytics, and artificial intelligence
* OpenText cloud APIs MUST be a key component of your solution

***

**Thank you for participating! We invite you to participate in one or all of the challenges identified. If you would like to combine multiple challenges into a super solution, submissions will be accepted and will be judged based on the use cases.**

### Task

* Develop a solution using OpenText API's
* Deployment of project on Github or Postman

***

### Submission format

* Project description (mandatory)
* Presentation (mandatory ‚Äì can be either a video or document)
* Link to the project

title: Unlocking the power of community data
description:
In today's interconnected world, communities generate an astonishing amount of data through their interactions, activities, and shared experiences. This data holds the key to unlocking insights, identifying patterns, and shaping strategies that can revolutionize numerous sectors, including healthcare, education, urban planning, and social services.
"Unlocking the Power of Community Data" will illuminate the pathways towards utilizing this vast resource effectively. Attendees will have the opportunity to learn from experts who have successfully harnessed community data to drive innovation, foster collaboration, and address critical challenges.

title: R Package Development Workflow
description:
Are you interested in learning about R package development workflow? Join us for an exciting event with Dr. Emi Tanaka, Senior Lecturer in Statistics at Monash University, Australia, as she takes us through the process of developing an R package.

Hosted by R-Ladies Lagos and R-Ladies Paris, this event promises to be a fun-filled and informative session for everyone. Dr. Tanaka will guide us through the workflow of creating and maintaining R packages, sharing her vast experience in the field.
At the end of the session, there will be a question and answer session where you can interact with Dr. Tanaka and clarify any doubts you may have. Plus, there will be a raffle draw where lucky winners will get amazing prizes.

Don't miss out on this incredible opportunity to learn from one of the best in the field of statistics. Register now and join us for an exciting session on R package development workflow with Dr. Emi Tanaka.

title: Women in Community International Women‚Äôs Day
description:
